<h3 id=3D"Requirements5.4-Approvedstacks">Approved stacks</h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(79,79,79);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(79,79,79=
);">These stacks are also tested, however not as extensively as our referen=
ce stack</span><span>.</span>&nbsp;These stacks still benefit from the full=
 support and maintenance guarantees provided with the eZ Publish Platform S=
ubscription, but more issues <em>might</em> occur during normal operations =
and issues might in some cases take longer to resolve. However approved sta=
cks with newer versions of MySQL and PHP will typically give you better per=
formance than the standard reference platform.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(79,79,79);">The supported non-reference stacks=
 for eZ Publish Platform 5 are:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Debian</strong></li>
<li><strong>Ubuntu</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(79,79,79);">The details of the approved stacks=
 can be seen in the table below, everything uses officially packages unless=
 mentioned otherwise.</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">&nbsp;</sp=
an></p>
