f the Symfony framework is bundled with the eZ Publish release.<br>eZ suppo=
rt eZ Publish only when used with the latest maintenance version of Symfony=
 within the version specified above, new maintenance versions are announced=
 by&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://symfony.com/blog/categor=
y/releases" rel=3D"nofollow">Symfony</a>&nbsp;and provided via composer. Sy=
mfony is not supported directly by eZ within eZ Publish Enterprise Subscrip=
tions, however contact your eZ Systems representative for alternatives.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Requirements5.4-Communitystacks-TechnicallysupportedbyeZPublishPl=
atform">Community stacks -&nbsp;<em>Technically supported by eZ Publish Pla=
tform</em></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(79,79,79);">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color:=
 rgb(79,79,79);">eZ Publish <em>(and especially the future eZ Platform)</em=
> can </span>theoretically<span style=3D"color: rgb(79,79,79);"> run and ex=
ecute on many more platforms than the ones listed as Enterprise Stacks, inc=
luding (but not limited to) the operating systems listing below if they pas=
s the&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/reference/requi=
rements.html" style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Symfony requirements</a><span style=3D"color: rgb(79,79,79);"=
>, using cache solutions technically supported by&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"ht=
tp://www.stashphp.com/Drivers.html" style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Stash</a>,&nbsp;using databases support=
ed by&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://doctrine-dbal.readthedocs.org/en/latest/refere=
nce/configuration.html#driver" style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Doctrine DBAL</a>, and using a binary file s=
torage solution supported by <a href=3D"https://github.com/thephpleague/fly=
system#adapters" style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;" class=3D"external-link" =
rel=3D"nofollow">FlySystem</a>&nbsp;(however eZ Publish 5.x is limited by l=
egacy cluster system here, so nfs is only choice is practice for cluster se=
tup).</p>
<p><strong>Note: eZ Systems doesn't insure or guarantee quality operation o=
f an eZ Publish Platform installation if it is running on a platform not li=
sted as&nbsp;professionally&nbsp;supported.</strong>&nbsp;eZ Publish Enterp=
rise Subscriptions are still available for compatible platforms, but the gu=
arantee and the product support will not apply and although you will receiv=
e various maintenance releases and services, no bug fix guarantee will appl=
y to issues related to the platform. Maintenance and monitoring tools will =
not be available. eZ Systems does not advise merely compatible platforms fo=
r production use.</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">However&nbsp;compatible platforms are=
 community supported, meaning contributions and efforts made to improve sup=
port for these technologies are welcome and can contribute to the technolog=
y being professionally supported by the eZ Systems team in the future.</spa=
n></p>
